Rake task for backing up mongo database on heroku and push it to S3.

== INSTALL

Add to Gemfile:

  gem "heroku-mongo-backup", :git => 'git://github.com/alexkravets/heroku-mongo-backup.git'

or

  gem "heroku-mongo-backup", "~> 0.1.2"


Add to application class in /config/application.rb file:

  require 'heroku_mongo_backup'


== BACKUP COMMAND

  rake mongo:backup
  
== RESTORE COMMAND

  rake mongo:restore FILE=<backup-file.gz>